{"segment_id": "00004", "page_num": 4, "segment": "an\n\nto monitoring,\nengineer’s\n“is book provides\ntroubleshooting, and debugging conversations .... Heuristics such as the\nQuestion Fraction are amazing---at the same time simple and memorable\nand incredibly insightful. Read this book to turn your communication\nskills into superpowers.”\n\napproach\n\n---Gojko Adžić, Author, and Partner at Neuri\nConsulting\n\n“Vital reading for anyone in a leadership role or interested in improving\ntheir work culture in general.”\n\n---Andy Skipper, Chief Coach at CTO Craft\n\n“If you’re looking for a practical framework and techniques that will help\nx broken team communication and dysfunctional culture, then you\nshould read Agile Conversations. Going beyond simple diagnosis, this\nhandbook walks you through the Five Conversations you need to embrace\nin order to transform a broken culture into one that’s healthy and highperforming.”\n\n---Paul Joyce, Founder and CEO, Geckoboard\n\n“Squirrel and Jeffrey’s keen writing and battle-tested techniques make this\nbook a must-read for modern engineering leaders looking to thrive amid\nthe explosion of complexity that we all face.”\n\n---Chris Cleareld, Co-Author of Meltdown: What\nPlane Crashes, Oil Spills, and Dumb Business Decisions\nCan Teach Us About How to Succeed at Work and at\nHome", "source_file": "Agile_Conversations_-_Douglas_SquirrelJeffrey_Fredrick.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": null, "chapter_title": null, "section_num": null, "section_title": null, "l1_summary": "to monitoring,\nengineer’s\n“is book provides\ntroubleshooting, and debugging conversations .... Read this book to turn your communication\nskills into superpowers.” “If you’re looking for a practical framework and techniques that will help\nx broken team communication and dysfunctional culture, then...", "l2_summary": "to monitoring,\nengineer’s\n“is book provides\ntroubleshooting, and debug