{"segment_id": "00048", "page_num": 48, "segment": "S: T C F\n\nCynefin is a sense-making framework whose goal is to allow shared\nunderstandings to emerge and to improve decision-making (see Figure 1.1).\n\nFigure 1.1: The Cynefin Framework\n\nWhile there are a rich set of activities and applications in the Cynefin\ncommunity, the first lesson of the framework is that appropriate behavior\ndepends on which domain you find yourself in.\n\n• When the situation is Obvious (causes and their eects are well\nunderstood), tools such as flowcharts are useful, because there\nare a limited number of possibilities, and the current state\ndetermines the next right step.\n\n• When the situation is Complicated (causes and eects are\nknown but only to specialists), with intricate needs such as\nin a sophisticated\ntroubleshooting unexpected behavior", "source_file": "Agile_Conversations_-_Douglas_SquirrelJeffrey_Fredrick.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "5", "chapter_title": "e Why Conversation", "section_num": null, "section_title": null, "l1_summary": "Cynefin is a sense-making framework whose goal is to allow shared\nunderstandings to emerge and to improve decision-making (see Figure 1.1). Figure 1.1: The Cynefin Framework While there are a rich set of activities and applications in the Cynefin\ncommunity, the first lesson of the framework is that...", "l2_summary": "Cynefin is a sense-making framework whose goal is to allow shared\nunderstandings to emerge and to improve decision-making (see Figure 1.1). Figure 1.1: The Cynefin Framework While there are a rich set of activities and applications in the Cynefin\ncommunity, the first lesson of the framework is that appropriate behavior\ndepends on which domain you find yourself in. • When the situation is Obvious (causes and their eects are well\nunderstood), tools such as flowcharts are useful, because there\nare a limited number of possibilities