{"segment_id": "00050", "page_num": 50, "segment": "Improving Your\nConversations\n\nT\n\nhis chapter will prepare you for the key relationship-building conversations\nyou need in order to escape the feature factory: the Trust Conversation, the\nFear Conversation, the Why Conversation, the Commitment Conversation, and\nthe Accountability Conversation. Before you tackle the specic conversations,\nhowever, it is important to learn how to analyze and build your conversational\nskills generally. You will learn about why conversations are humanity’s unique\nsuperpower and how to harness this power effectively through study and\npractice.\n\nis chapter will also describe the core challenge to improving our\nconversations, which is that our behavior doesn’t match our beliefs, and we are\nunaware of the gap. To combat this problem, we will provide a process to help\nyou become aware: the Four Rs. We will show you how to Record your", "source_file": "Agile_Conversations_-_Douglas_SquirrelJeffrey_Fredrick.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "5", "chapter_title": "e Why Conversation", "section_num": null, "section_title": null, "l1_summary": "Improving Your\nConversations his chapter will prepare you for the key relationship-building conversations\nyou need in order to escape the feature factory: the Trust Conversation, the\nFear Conversation, the Why Conversation, the Commitment Conversation, and\nthe Accountability Conversation. We will...", "l2_summary": "Improving Your\nConversations his chapter will prepare you for the key relationship-building conversations\nyou need in order to escape the feature factory: the Trust Conversation, the\nFear Conversation, the Why Conversation, the Commitment Conversation, and\nthe Accountability Conversation. Before you tackle the specic conversations,\nhowever, it is important to learn how to analyze and build your conversational\nskills generally. You will learn about why convers