{"segment_id": "00246", "page_num": 246, "segment": "I’m Right, You’re Wrong, Now What?: Break the Impasse and Get What\nYou Need by Dr. Xavier Amador describes the model he developed\nwhile providing therapy for people in denial to the general public:\nLEAP\nis\nconversational and, we believe, is both similar to and applicable for\nthe methods we describe in this book.\n\n(Listen-Empathize-Agree-Partner). is\n\napproach\n\nNonviolent Communication: A Language of Life by Marshall B.\nRosenberg, PhD, is more than an approach to communication; it is a\nphilosophy for living. However, even people skeptical of this\nphilosophy can nd some very useful exercises to reect on their\ncommunication and their mind-set.\n\nVideo and Audio\n\non\n\nthe\n\nweek\n\nTroubleshooting\n\nEvery\npodcast\n(https://troubleshootingagile.com), we discuss relevant, current\ntopics in Agile, Lean, and DevOps teams, offering ideas and\nsolutions for improving delivery and communication in software\nteams.\n\nAgile\n\ne weekly Feeling Good podcast by Dr. David Burns\n(https://feelinggood.com/list-of-feeling-good-podcasts/)\nregularly\nprovides excellent real-life examples of how changing conversations\nchanges relationships. Particularly relevant are the episodes\ncovering e Five Secrets of Communication and the Interpersonal\nModel.\n\ne\nConversationalTransformation.com, has\n\ncompanion\n\nwebsite\n\nfor\n\nthis\n\nbook,\nfollow-up materials,", "source_file": "Agile_Conversations_-_Douglas_SquirrelJeffrey_Fredrick.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "5", "chapter_title": "e Why Conversation", "section_num": null, "section_title": null, "l1_summary": "Nonviolent Communication: A Language of Life by Marshall B. Rosenberg, PhD, is more than an approach to communication; it is a\nphilosophy for living. e weekly Feeling Good podcast by Dr.", "l2_summary": "I’m Right, You’re Wrong, Now What?: Break the Impasse and Get What\nYou Need b